Ableton Live MIDI Remote Script for MIDI Fighter 3D from DJ Tech Tools

-----------
DESCRIPTION
-----------

This script creates the so called 4x4 "RED Box" and mapps it to the MF3D. The color of the clips in Ableton live are displaced on the MF3D.

-----
SETUP
-----

1. Copy the downloaded folder "MF3D_Color_Clip" into your Ableton Live's MIDI Remote Scripts folder. 
Located in C:\Program Files (x86)\Ableton\Live x.x\Resources\MIDI Remote Scripts\ under Windos or
\Live x.x\Live.app\Contents\App-Resources\MIDI Remote Scripts\ for Mac OSX

2. Launch Ableton Live and go to Preferences. Under MIDI Sync tab select MF3D Color Clip in the Control Surface drop down list and set the 
correct input and output MIDI ports.


